House Resolution 528
By: Representative Carter of the 93rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Reverend Shivern L. Jeter; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Reverend Shivern L. Jeter has long been recognized by the citizens of this state
3 for the vital role that she has played in leadership and her deep personal commitment to the
4 welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, Reverend Jeter is an Associate Minister at The Historic Macedonia Baptist
6 Church, in Conyers, Georgia; a Housing Support Coordinator for View Point Health; and
7 an outstanding community leader; and
8 WHEREAS, she has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours of her time,
9 talents, and energy toward the betterment of her community and state as evidenced
10 dramatically by her superlative service with Foster Care Friends, Inc.; and
11 WHEREAS, Reverend Jeter is a faithful foster parent of 28 years, as well as the founder and
12 executive director of Foster Care Friends, Inc., a nonprofit that supports the foster, adoption,
13 kinship, and homeless community; and
