14 WHEREAS, on April 1, 2025 Foster Care Friends, Inc., will celebrate 11 years of exemplary
15 service and dedication to children and families in need; and
16 WHEREAS, Reverend Jeter 's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable
17 patience and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of
18 this state have earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues and associates; and
19 WHEREAS, Reverend Jeter additionally serves her community as an Executive Board
20 member for The Department of Family and Children Services, Advisory Chaplain at
21 Rockdale Piedmont Hospital, Sworn Court Appointed Specialty Advocate for children in
22 Rockdale County, Assistant Chaplain at the Rockdale Sheriff's Department, and as a Council
23 Board Member for Rockdale County Public Schools; and
24 WHEREAS, she is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
25 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
27 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Shivern L. Jeter for her
30 efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of Georgia;
31 congratulate her upon the grand occasion of the 11th anniversary of Foster Care Friends, Inc.;
32 and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
